If you decide to withdraw from the Integrated smoking cessation and breastfeeding program study, what will be the impact on your medical care at the institution?
A) You will be charged a penalty fee for withdrawing; 
B) Your current or future care at the institution will not be affected, and you will not lose any benefits to which you are entitled; 
C) You will be prohibited from participating in any other research studies at the institution; 
D) Your medical records will be flagged, preventing you from receiving standard medical care.

Correct answer: B

Which of the following interventions is considered experimental in the Integrated smoking cessation and breastfeeding program study?
A) Standard prenatal care and postpartum follow-up;
B) Referral to the New York State Smokers' Quitline and the Special Supplemental Nutrition Program for Women, Infants, and Children (WIC);
C) The integrated intervention of smoking cessation and breastfeeding, including education, counseling, monitoring, feedback, and contingent incentives;
D) Observations of mother-infant interactions during free play in the clinic.

Correct answer: C
